---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---

<BaseLayout title="Flight Tracker — Peter Hou" description="Live flight tracker">
  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="title">Flight Tracker</h1>
      <p class="intro">
        When your beloved ones are on a flight, you want to know — is it on schedule? Did they depart? Did they land?
        I built this project so I can add their flight and get a Telegram notification at every stage:
        departure (left the gate), airborne (wheels off), landed (touchdown), and arrived (at the gate).
        I hope they receive the same notifications when I'm the one flying.
        It's a small thing, but knowing your beloved ones landed safely without having to ask "Did you land?" is worth the entire project.
      </p>
      <p class="intro">
        Plus, you can follow the live position of the flight, which makes the experience fun.
        I also realized this app doubles as a personal flight record — remarkable if you fly often.
        Looking through those past flights brings back the memories and stories. They're all bonuses.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <div class="embed">
    <iframe
      src="https://myflighttracker.fly.dev/"
      title="Flight Tracker"
      allowfullscreen
    ></iframe>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-section {
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .intro + .intro {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }


  .embed {
    flex: 1;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  iframe {
    flex: 1;
    width: 100%;
    min-height: 80vh;
    border: none;
  }
</style>
